reviews.review_text: Killer Show I was 17 at this show.  The light show during drum space was amazing.  They had these street sign lights swirling around on the croud.  The drummers had these suits on that had red and white lights on them so they looked like traffic on the stage.  Great light show compared to any Denver show I went to.  Great version of Shakedown Street.  Not the best recording, but not awfull.  I would recommend this show.

my first west coast show I have seen around 25-30 east coast shows prior to this
 I brought a friend with me who never seen the dead before
 he had a great time although i was not very impressed with
the shows 12-12 and 12-13-1993.  the parking lot seen was
in a word insane the sports arena on thursday thru sunday
have a swap-meet which is endless shopping so it was
pretty cool seeing dead-heads trading and mingling with
the people at the swap-meet in the lot. it was a ok show
but had higher standards for this show being in cali....
I did get to JGB in san diego at balboa park at the starlight bowl
and that show was way better than these shows.  does anyone
have a copy of JGB in san diego 1994  if so let me know.......

First Dead Show I was 8 when I went to this show with my Mom. I remember it as being amazing and I rocked my little heart out the entire time. Until I fell asleep during Space. Mom assured me I was not the first person to have done that.
